# Agentic Marketer — environment variables
#
# ALL of these are optional. With none set, the app uses your logged-in Claude
# CLI session for the Agent SDK and assumes it is served at http://localhost:4400.
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (git-ignored) and uncomment what you need.

# --- Claude authentication (pick at most one; precedence is top-to-bottom) ---
# A pay-per-token Anthropic API key (sk-ant-...). Highest precedence.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
#
# A Claude Code OAuth token from `claude setup-token` (uses your subscription).
# Used only if ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is unset.
# CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=...
#
# If neither is set, the app falls back to your logged-in `claude` CLI session.
# (You can also paste a token at runtime via the Connect dialog in the UI.)

# --- Google Ads API version (optional) ---
# Google sunsets API versions ~yearly; a sunset version returns a 404 HTML page.
# Defaults to a current version. If launches start failing with a version/404
# error, find a live one (curl googleads.googleapis.com/vNN/… → 401 = live, 404 =
# gone) and set it here.
# GOOGLE_ADS_API_VERSION=v21

# --- Model ---
# Pin a specific model for the agents. Defaults to your Claude Code default.
# AGENT_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8

# --- App base URL ---
# Public origin of this app. Used to build email unsubscribe links and the
# webhook result callback URL. Defaults to http://localhost:4400.
# Set this if you host the app somewhere else.
# APP_BASE_URL=http://localhost:4400

# --- OAuth public URL (for tunnels) ---
# Providers like Meta reject localhost redirect URIs and require a real HTTPS
# domain. When running behind a tunnel (ngrok/cloudflared), set this to the
# tunnel's https URL so the OAuth redirect_uri is deterministic and matches what
# you register with the provider. Falls back to APP_BASE_URL, then request origin.
# OAUTH_PUBLIC_URL=https://your-subdomain.ngrok-free.app

# --- Channel credentials ---
# NOTE: X / LinkedIn / Reddit / Mastodon / Meta credentials are NOT set here.
# You connect those per-project at runtime under the ⚙ Channels button (OAuth),
# and the tokens are stored locally in ./data/marketer.db (git-ignored).
